# Rendshot — Image Generation Skills

When the user asks to generate images, create social media graphics, take screenshots, or work with visual content, use the Rendshot API or MCP tools.

## Available Tools (MCP)
- `generate_image` — Render HTML, fill templates, or AI-generate from prompt
- `screenshot_url` — Capture webpages
- `list_templates` / `get_template` — Browse and inspect templates
- `create_template` — Save designs for reuse

## Quick Start
```
# AI prompt mode (most powerful — generates design from natural language)
generate_image({ prompt: "Coffee shop promo card, warm tones", platform: "instagram_post" })

# Template mode (deterministic — fill variables in a saved template)
generate_image({ template_id: "tpl_xxx", variables: { title: "Hello" } })
```

## Platform Presets
xiaohongshu (1080x1440), xiaohongshu_wide (1080x810), instagram_post (1080x1080), instagram_story (1080x1920), twitter_card (1200x628), twitter_post (1200x675), linkedin_post (1200x627), youtube_thumb (1280x720), wechat_cover (900x383), wechat_thumb (200x200), og_image (1200x630), custom (1080x1080)

## For detailed guides, see:
- skills/rendshot/ — Tool usage reference
